> Is it possible we re-arrange columns in intermediate stage instead if we pass data schema to intermediate stage? This way we can leave the leaf stage untouched.

@61yao no it isn't, I tried that for the initial PR but we generate data schemas based on the result of the calcite logical plan. I tried hacking calcite to allow that behavior and it gets really brittle (it complains during the validation phase that the expected schema and the operator schema don't match up)

also, fwiw, I think Calcite is right here. Each logical node should be correct independently - we shouldn't make assumptions about the physical execution when building the logical plan.

@zhtaoxiang @snleee Correct, the `maxValidBucketEndTimeMs` is only used for the lowest level. 

- For the lowest level, the delay is calculated as (maxValidBucketEndTimeMs - waterMark) / bucketTime
- For other levels, we do (lowerLevelWatermark - waterMark) / bucketTime

@zhtaoxiang Thanks for catching this, this looks good to me.

@61yao merging this first to unblock some other PRs. please let me know if anything else requires follow up.

> Can we also add query option to disable shuffle if needed. So we can know 1) the performance gain from this 2) remove the shuffle when we see an issue

yes this can be done in follow up PRs.

@huang1st Sorry I lost track of this issue. Did you find the cause of the issue?
Is the `value` column always whole number in the input data? What is the rough cardinality (unique values) of the column?
Most likely the issue is caused by #8722, but I don't see why it doesn't work. If you can reproduce it, can you try reverting this commit and see if the issue is fixed?
